	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Behind the numbers is a generational thread: the father-wound. A man who was never fathered well — who never heard "I'm proud of you," who learned love as performance or absence — carries that ache into his own home, often without meaning to. He fathers out of an empty tank, repeating what he swore he would never repeat, or working himself numb to prove he is enough.</p><p>These are not signs of a bad man or a failed dad. They are the marks of a son who was never fully fathered, now trying to give what he never received. There is a Father who sees the wound beneath the striving — and who fathers the father first.</p>`}
	painsSources={[
