	aFatherHeading={`A Father for fathers`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>The answer to a weary, striving, or wounded dad is not a better technique, a stricter schedule, or trying harder to be the father you never had. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a holy, perfect Father for a beloved son who happens to be raising children of his own.</p><p>Every man fathers out of what he received. You cannot give a fathering you have not been given. If your own father was absent, harsh, or simply human and limited, there is a tank in you that runs dry — and no amount of effort fills it from the inside. It has to be filled from above.</p><p>So before you are a provider, before you are a disciplinarian, before you are the strong one everyone leans on, you are a son. Your heavenly Father wants to father <em>you</em> — to heal the orphan ache, to say the words you never heard, to delight in you. And the love that finally fills you is the love that will overflow, unforced, onto your kids.</p>`}
