	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; Hudson Taylor, Andrew Murray, and Charles Spurgeon (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You may not see the fruit of your fathering for years. The prayers whispered over a crib, the patience held onto through a hard season, the love shown when it was not returned — none of it is wasted. Our Father's Word, sown into your home, does what He sends it to do.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What the Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"Son, before you ever held your child, I held you. Before you were a father, you were Mine — and you still are. I know the dad who raised you. I saw what you were given and what you were never given. I am not asking you to manufacture a love you never received. I am offering to be its Source.</p><p>Come and let Me father you. Let Me say the words you never heard: I see you. I am proud of you. I delight in you — not for what you provide, but because you are My son. Let Me heal the ache you've carried so long. Then go home and father your children, not from your own empty strength, but from the love I am pouring into you. You don't have to be perfect. You only have to keep coming to Me. I am your Father, and you are Mine."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for fathers`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You and praise You for all fathers — the men who provide and protect, who carry worry no one sees, who long to give their children more than they themselves received. Let them hear Your whisper above every voice that says they are not enough. Let them encounter Your love — not as a duty they perform, but as a weight they feel — and experience Your delight over them, apart from their providing, their discipline, or their success.</p><p>Give them grace to prioritize intimacy with You above their striving, and to receive their identity as Your sons before they ever step into the role of father. Father, heal the father-wound in them — the absence, the harshness, the words never spoken. Fill the empty tank, so the love they pour onto their children overflows from the love You pour onto them. Turn their hearts to their children and their children's hearts to them.</p><p>I pray Your protection over them from the enemy, from temptation, from the lie that they must father alone, and from despair. Let them know there is no condemnation in You — that when they fail, You restore, as the father ran to the prodigal. Let them know You, their Father, as their true inheritance and reward, for every other gift pales beside the gift of You. And may they wake up every single day under the pour of their heavenly Father's heart for them.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
