	keepReadingHtml={`Begin with the <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">whole Bible free online with audio</a>, learn <a href="/the-fathers-heart-bible/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">why the Father's Heart Bible™ exists</a>, or get oriented with our <a href="/guides/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Bible reading guides</a> — including <a href="/guides/how-to-pray/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">how to pray</a> and <a href="/verses/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">verses by topic</a>. Or meet others learning to love from the Father's overflow in <a href="/bible-for/mothers/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">the Bible for mothers</a> and <a href="/bible-for/husbands/" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">the Bible for husbands</a>.`}
	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for fathers?`, answer: `Psalm 103:13 (as a father shows compassion), Romans 8:15 and Galatians 4:6 (the Spirit of adoption crying "Abba, Father"), Luke 15:20 (the father runs to the prodigal), Ephesians 3:14-15 (every family named from the Father), Psalm 68:5 (Father of the fatherless), and Malachi 4:6 (hearts of fathers turned to their children) all speak straight to dads. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about the father-wound?`, answer: `Scripture is honest that human fathers fail and wound — and it offers a perfect Father who heals. Psalm 68:5 calls God "Father of the fatherless," Jesus promises in John 14:18 "I will not leave you as orphans," and Luke 15 shows a father running to embrace a son who felt unworthy. In the Father's Heart Bible™ you can read these passages free, with audio, and meet the Father whose love heals what your own father could not give.` },
		{ question: `How can I be a good father when I had a bad one?`, answer: `You cannot give a fathering you have not received — but you can receive it now. The Bible's answer is not to try harder in your own strength; it is to be adopted and fathered by God (Romans 8:15), filled by His love, and to father your children from that overflow (Ephesians 3:14-19). Many dads start by simply reading the Father's Heart Bible™ daily to be fathered, not to perform — letting God fill the tank they pour from.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free online Bible with audio for dads?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on any phone or computer and read or hear any book — perfect for a busy dad to listen on the commute or read a few minutes before bed.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different for fathers?`, answer: `It is the first English translation to reveal God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so the God you read has a Father's face. For a dad, especially one carrying a father-wound, that reframes everything: you come to the text first as a beloved son being fathered, and learn fatherhood from the perfect Father before you give it to your kids.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say to a father who feels like he's failing?`, answer: `You are in good company — Scripture is full of imperfect fathers, and a Father who restores. The prodigal's father in Luke 15 runs to embrace a son who expected rejection, and Psalm 103:13 says God's compassion toward you is like a father's toward his children. If you feel you're falling short, the Father's Heart Bible™ lets you read those passages free, with audio, and meet a Father who fathers you so you can father them.` },
		{ question: `What Bible verses help heal an absent or distant father relationship?`, answer: `Malachi 4:6 promises God turns "the hearts of fathers to their children and the hearts of children to their fathers," Psalm 68:5 names God "Father of the fatherless," and 2 Corinthians 6:18 records His promise: "I will be a Father to you." These verses, read free with audio in the Father's Heart Bible™, point both to reconciliation with an earthly father and to the perfect Father who fills every gap an earthly one left.` },
	]}
